        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/23/2/233/1",
        "text": [
          ": مَنْ قَرَأَ فِی الْفَرِیضَهِ سُورَهَ الْمُدَّثِّرِ کَانَ حَقّاً عَلَی اللَّهِ عَزَّ وَ جَلَّ أَنْ یَجْعَلَهُ مَعَ مُحَمَّدٍ ص فِی دَرَجَتِهِ وَ لَا یُدْرِکُهُ فِی حَیَاهِ الدُّنْیَا شَقَاءٌ أَبَداً إِنْ شَاءَ اللَّهُ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-athar-husain-rizvi-&-sayed-maqsood-athar": [
            "1. From the previous chain from al-Hassan from ’Asim al-Khayyat from Muhammad b. Muslim from Abi Ja’far Muhammad al-Baqir (a.s.) who said: Imam Muhammad Baqir (a.s.), “One who recites Surah Muddassir in his obligatory Salaat it is the duty of Allah to give him a status along with Muhammad (s.a.w.s.) and he will not face any difficulty in his worldly life, God-Willing.”"
          ]
        }
      }
